  • Constructor Details

    • Pokemon

      public Pokemon(String pokemonName, int PokedexNumber, PokemonTypesManager pokemonTypes, Integer nextEvolutionLevel, BigDecimal pokemonWeightPounds, BigDecimal pokemonHeightMeters, Boolean pokemonIsCaught, String pokedexEntry)
      Class Constructor Used to create a Pokémon. Calls the method formatPokemonName() for the Pokémon name.
      Parameters:
      pokemonName - String Pokémon name
      PokedexNumber - int Pokédex number
      pokemonTypes - PokemonTypesManager Pokémon types (1 or 2)
      nextEvolutionLevel - Integer The level the Pokémon will evolve (can be null or 0 if the Pokémon does not evolve.
      pokemonWeightPounds - BigDecimal weight of the Pokémon
      pokemonHeightMeters - BigDecimal height of the Pokémon
      pokemonIsCaught - Boolean Has the Pokémon been caught or not
      pokedexEntry - String A short sentence or two about the Pokémon in the Pokédex

    • hasNextEvolution

      public String hasNextEvolution()
      Checks to see if the nextEvolution variable is null or 0. If null, it prints "FULLY EVOLVED"
      Returns:
      String with either the Pokédex Next Evolution level or "NO NEXT EVOLUTION."

    • hasPokedexEntry

      public String hasPokedexEntry()
      Checks to see if the Pokédex entry is null. If null, it prints "NO POKÉDEX ENTRY."
      Returns:
      String with either the Pokédex Entry or "NO POKÉDEX ENTRY."
